WEBVTT

00:00.294 --> 00:01.569
<i>John: Previously on "Switched at Birth"...</i>

00:01.579 --> 00:03.835
Wow, I can't believe you made all of these.

00:03.997 --> 00:05.931
Do you know your sister is, like, a genius?

00:06.704 --> 00:08.119
_

00:08.122 --> 00:09.802
I need to ask for an
advance on my billings.

00:09.836 --> 00:11.070
- $50,000.
- Okay.

00:11.184 --> 00:13.886
Under one condition: You
work for me exclusively.

00:13.920 --> 00:14.887
Fine.

00:15.647 --> 00:17.786
_

00:19.060 --> 00:21.587
_

00:21.627 --> 00:22.060
Wow.

00:23.096 --> 00:24.096
I sold a book idea.

00:24.130 --> 00:25.197
And I wanna hear all about it.

00:25.331 --> 00:27.199
Kathryn, are you out of your mind?

00:27.233 --> 00:29.067
You are talking about intimate details

00:29.102 --> 00:31.036
of our friends' lives.

00:31.070 --> 00:33.005
- My mom... she didn't show up for work.
- Is everything okay?

00:33.099 --> 00:36.068
I was just so sick of looking at that wall.

00:36.102 --> 00:37.336
Her mom is mentally ill.

00:37.490 --> 00:39.391
Stop! If you wanna be a friend to me,

00:39.425 --> 00:41.593
promise you'll leave this alone.

00:41.627 --> 00:43.395
This guy I was gonna see
tonight just bailed on me.

00:43.429 --> 00:44.529
You can join me if you want.

00:46.432 --> 00:47.599
<i>Toby: Does someone wanna
tell me what's going on here?</i>

00:47.700 --> 00:50.335
I kissed your father.

00:50.369 --> 00:51.503
It was a stupid, drunken kiss.

00:51.537 --> 00:52.637
I want you out of here!

00:57.011 --> 00:59.578
<i>Woman on TV: Welcome back on
this beautiful day in Kansas City.</i>

00:59.612 --> 01:01.446
<i>Good morning, everybody.
Coming up, a local chef</i>

01:01.481 --> 01:03.348
<i>stops by to show us what to...</i>

01:04.584 --> 01:07.219
<i>- (Softly groans)
- Rise and shine.</i>

01:07.253 --> 01:09.221
(Groaning) Oh, man,

01:09.255 --> 01:11.223
I am buying you a new couch.

01:11.257 --> 01:12.390
<i>- (TV turns off)
- Oh.</i>

01:12.425 --> 01:14.459
Or you could just go
home and apologize to mom

01:14.494 --> 01:16.294
for making out with my mother-in-law.

01:16.329 --> 01:19.297
I told you last night Jennice kissed me.

01:19.332 --> 01:20.532
Just so you know, it's not gonna make

01:20.566 --> 01:23.401
your future grandkids' birthday
parties any less awkward.

01:23.436 --> 01:25.237
All right, I get it. I get it, all right?

01:25.271 --> 01:27.439
You know, I shouldn't have had her
over when your mom was outta town.

01:27.473 --> 01:29.407
Okay, I made a mistake.

01:29.442 --> 01:30.575
Yeah, you did.

01:30.610 --> 01:32.244
I don't even know what
I'm gonna tell Nikki.

01:32.278 --> 01:34.179
Well, there's nothing to tell.

01:34.213 --> 01:35.514
It didn't mean anything.

01:35.548 --> 01:37.516
It was a moment, and then it was gone.

01:37.550 --> 01:39.417
And that's, you know...

01:39.452 --> 01:40.585
try telling your mother that.

01:40.620 --> 01:43.388
Who, by the way, is
completely overreacting.

01:43.422 --> 01:45.390
So, uh...

01:45.424 --> 01:47.225
you just gonna live here forever?

01:47.260 --> 01:48.560
Nope.

01:48.594 --> 01:50.595
I think till your mother
comes to her senses

01:50.630 --> 01:52.597
and accepts my apology.

01:52.632 --> 01:54.299
(Groans loudly)

01:54.333 --> 01:55.500
Shouldn't be too long.

01:55.535 --> 01:59.171
It's just, you know,
this place isn't that big.

01:59.205 --> 02:02.307
And I kinda need my living room to...

02:02.341 --> 02:04.142
live in.

02:04.177 --> 02:06.311
Come on, it's gonna be fun.

02:06.345 --> 02:08.513
<i>Oh-ho, when I was in the minors,</i>

02:08.548 --> 02:11.349
they used to cram us
in, four guys to a room.

02:11.384 --> 02:13.118
And you know what?

02:13.152 --> 02:15.320
Those were some of the
best times of my life.

02:15.354 --> 02:16.555
(Chuckles)

02:16.589 --> 02:17.589
You know what we're gonna do?

02:17.623 --> 02:19.491
We're gonna start this day

02:19.525 --> 02:22.594
the way me and boys used
to back in the day...

02:22.628 --> 02:24.262
with a doubleheader.

02:24.297 --> 02:26.531
Four eggs, four pieces of toast,

02:26.566 --> 02:27.566
<i>hash browns.</i>

02:27.600 --> 02:29.501
You put it all on a big bed of bacon.

02:29.535 --> 02:31.503
And I'm talking real bacon, my friend.

02:31.537 --> 02:34.573
Not that turkey crap your
mom has in the kitchen.

02:34.607 --> 02:36.575
You got a frying pan around here somewhere?

02:42.315 --> 02:43.415
- Hi.
- Morning, honey.

02:43.449 --> 02:45.250
- You hungry?
- Not really.

02:45.284 --> 02:46.585
But it looks like you're covered in case

02:46.619 --> 02:48.587
<i>the rest of the neighborhood stops by.</i>

02:48.621 --> 02:50.422
I couldn't sleep last night. (Sighs)

02:50.456 --> 02:54.159
Well, notice anything different about me?

02:54.193 --> 02:56.261
- You got your hand back.
- Mm-hmm.

02:56.295 --> 02:58.363
Yep. And check out my cool scar.

02:58.397 --> 03:01.333
I'm thinking of telling
people I had stigmata.

03:01.367 --> 03:03.401
You know, you still have to rest it.

03:03.436 --> 03:05.170
I will. Hey, where's dad?

03:05.204 --> 03:06.338
He's gonna wanna see this.
You know how he's always

03:06.372 --> 03:08.540
- bragging about that scar on his knee.
- I...

03:08.574 --> 03:12.277
You know, I think your dad
had an early tee time today.

03:12.311 --> 03:14.412
All right, I guess I'll text him a picture.

03:14.447 --> 03:16.114
<i>(Door closes)</i>

03:16.148 --> 03:17.115
<i>Toby: Hey.</i>

03:17.149 --> 03:18.383
Morning, honey.

03:18.417 --> 03:19.551
Here to pick up some clothes.

03:19.585 --> 03:21.419
Didn't you move all your stuff already?

03:21.454 --> 03:24.189
Not for me.

03:24.223 --> 03:25.323
I'll take care of it.

03:28.194 --> 03:29.427
Okay, what's going on?

03:29.462 --> 03:31.229
I thought you knew.

03:32.298 --> 03:34.366
Last night mom and dad had a big fight.

03:37.570 --> 03:39.237
She kicked him out.

