09:14.196 --> 09:15.329
Yo, Sharee.

09:15.364 --> 09:16.330
Is that your mom?

09:26.475 --> 09:27.442
Mom, what are you doing here?

09:27.476 --> 09:29.377
You know damn well why I'm here.

09:29.411 --> 09:31.579
- No, I don't.
- You didn't make your bed this morning!

09:35.217 --> 09:37.218
I'm sorry. Okay, I forgot.

09:37.252 --> 09:39.654
Oh, that's your excuse?
You are such a slob.

09:39.688 --> 09:41.322
<i>It's disgusting.</i>

09:41.356 --> 09:42.457
Mom, please.

09:42.491 --> 09:44.192
- Not here.
- Oh, why?

09:44.226 --> 09:46.194
Because of your friends?
You don't want them knowing

09:46.228 --> 09:47.662
- what a pig you are!
- Okay, I'll clean up tonight.

09:47.696 --> 09:50.398
- I promise.
- No, you're gonna do it right now.

09:50.432 --> 09:52.300
I can't just leave school.

09:52.334 --> 09:54.202
What if those guys from
the state come back?

09:55.404 --> 09:57.205
You think I'm gonna let
them take you away from me

09:57.239 --> 09:58.506
'cause our house is a mess?

09:58.540 --> 10:00.408
Get in the car now!

10:00.442 --> 10:01.676
Okay!

10:01.710 --> 10:03.644
Let me get my bag.

10:12.321 --> 10:14.322
- I don't think you should go.
- Trust me.

10:14.356 --> 10:16.591
When she's acting like this,
the best thing to do is go along.

10:16.625 --> 10:18.559
Sharee, she needs help.

10:18.594 --> 10:19.694
And so do you.

10:23.265 --> 10:24.298
I know.

10:29.471 --> 10:30.538
<i>(Car starts)</i>

10:38.115 --> 10:39.949
<i>I hope you're as excited about
what you've seen here today as I am.</i>

10:40.083 --> 10:41.217
<i>But at the end of the day,</i>

10:41.251 --> 10:42.885
<i>a building is just a building.</i>

10:42.919 --> 10:44.086
We'll do our best with
the bricks and mortar,

10:44.121 --> 10:46.222
but it's you people that
need to bring the magic,

10:46.386 --> 10:48.254
<i>that turns a development like this</i>

10:48.288 --> 10:50.222
<i>into a real community.</i>

10:50.257 --> 10:51.891
<i>And I truly believe that.</i>

10:51.925 --> 10:53.325
<i>Now before I take any questions,</i>

10:53.360 --> 10:55.928
<i>I wanted to introduce to you
someone special from my team.</i>

10:55.962 --> 10:58.898
She actually brought the property
to my attention in the first place.

10:58.932 --> 11:00.900
Without her, I'd probably be talking to

11:00.934 --> 11:02.101
"The friends of Prairie Heights" right now.

11:02.135 --> 11:03.202
(All chuckle)

11:03.236 --> 11:06.205
Give her a hand. East Riverside's own...

11:06.239 --> 11:07.306
Regina Vasquez.

11:07.340 --> 11:09.241
(Applause)

11:17.918 --> 11:19.051
Hey, Dr. Jackson.

11:19.085 --> 11:20.085
Can I talk to you for a second?

11:20.120 --> 11:21.887
I need some advice.

11:21.922 --> 11:23.989
Hmm, let's see.

11:24.024 --> 11:25.891
Jorge's got those eyes,

11:25.926 --> 11:27.960
but Campbell's got that smile.

11:27.994 --> 11:30.196
- Excuse me?
- Every time I turn around

11:30.230 --> 11:32.965
you're flirting with one
of the guys on my staff.

11:32.999 --> 11:34.300
You're here to serve your sentence.

11:34.334 --> 11:36.135
Instead, you treat this clinic like

11:36.169 --> 11:38.103
it's the set of "the dating game."

11:38.138 --> 11:39.939
Okay...

11:39.973 --> 11:41.941
I deserve that. (Exhales)

11:41.975 --> 11:43.108
I have this friend,

11:43.143 --> 11:45.110
and her mom has some mental problems.

11:45.145 --> 11:47.947
I barely have enough
time for my own patients.

11:47.981 --> 11:49.281
- Call the county.
- I already did.

11:49.316 --> 11:50.883
Please.

11:50.917 --> 11:52.318
She has nowhere else to go.

11:52.352 --> 11:54.253
(Exhales)

11:54.287 --> 11:55.988
(Sighs)

11:58.058 --> 11:59.258
(Sighs)

11:59.292 --> 12:01.293
So, with the widening of Higgins Street

12:01.328 --> 12:02.862
on the south side of the property,

12:02.896 --> 12:04.830
we expect traffic impact to be minimal.

12:04.865 --> 12:06.065
<i>Are there any other questions?</i>

12:06.099 --> 12:07.166
Yes, ma'am.

12:07.200 --> 12:08.300
Have you thought about what your project

12:08.335 --> 12:11.170
will do to East Riverside in the long run?

12:11.204 --> 12:12.972
<i>Well, I'm glad you asked that.</i>

12:13.006 --> 12:15.140
I expect property tax to bring
upwards of two million dollars

12:15.175 --> 12:16.942
into the city every year.

12:17.010 --> 12:18.010
<i>Not to mention sales tax,</i>

12:18.044 --> 12:19.178
dozens of new jobs.

12:19.212 --> 12:22.214
But what about the families that
have lived there for generations?

12:22.249 --> 12:25.851
Well, you know what they say:
All boats rise with the tide.

12:25.886 --> 12:27.152
<i>If they can afford to.</i>

12:27.187 --> 12:29.321
What happens when your project

12:29.356 --> 12:31.223
brings people with money
to the neighborhood,

12:31.258 --> 12:33.859
and landlords double our rent

12:33.894 --> 12:35.194
just because they can?

12:35.228 --> 12:36.195
(Clears throat)

12:36.229 --> 12:39.098
<i>That tax revenue I was talking
about... that's going back</i>

12:39.132 --> 12:41.100
into your parks and into your schools.

12:41.134 --> 12:42.134
<i>It's gonna make your neighborhood safer</i>

12:42.168 --> 12:43.969
for your kids and your grandkids.

12:44.004 --> 12:46.939
I mean, that's the real
future for East Riverside.

12:46.973 --> 12:48.274
<i>That's all the time I have for questions.</i>

12:48.308 --> 12:50.042
Thank you.

12:51.278 --> 12:54.880
- (Murmuring)
- (Whispering in Spanish)

13:03.023 --> 13:05.754
- When'd the tornado hit?
- This is all dad.

13:05.821 --> 13:06.692
He's like an animal.

13:06.693 --> 13:09.128
I have no idea how mom kept the
house together all these years.

13:09.382 --> 13:12.084
- Where is he?
- Uh, he's at the grocery store.

13:12.118 --> 13:13.085
Why?

13:13.119 --> 13:14.186
(Scoffs)

13:14.220 --> 13:15.454
Well, now that my hand's working again,

13:15.488 --> 13:17.422
I thought I'd slap some sense into him.

13:17.457 --> 13:19.324
You don't think I've tried?

13:19.359 --> 13:22.327
He thinks mom should be apologizing to him

13:22.362 --> 13:23.495
for kicking him out.

13:23.530 --> 13:26.365
This is so depressing. Are
any guys faithful anymore?

13:26.399 --> 13:28.167
Me.

13:28.201 --> 13:29.501
I'm like a monk.

13:29.636 --> 13:31.536
Do you think they're
gonna get through this?

13:31.571 --> 13:33.305
Of course.

13:33.339 --> 13:35.207
(Exhales)

13:35.241 --> 13:37.409
I was thinking about how I spent the summer

13:37.443 --> 13:38.577
living with Regina and Angelo,

13:38.611 --> 13:41.246
and it was great because...

13:41.281 --> 13:43.515
I always thought John
and Kathryn would be there

13:43.549 --> 13:45.284
to come home to, you know?

13:45.318 --> 13:47.252
Yeah.

13:47.287 --> 13:48.654
One of the reasons marrying
Nikki wasn't so scary

13:48.688 --> 13:50.622
was 'cause I was like,

13:50.657 --> 13:52.457
"mom and dad have made it so long,

13:52.492 --> 13:54.426
how hard can it be?"

13:56.362 --> 13:58.497
All those stupid Kennish family traditions

13:58.531 --> 14:00.432
that I pretend to hate...

14:00.466 --> 14:02.267
what if we never get to do those again?

14:05.204 --> 14:09.207
We've gotta get them talking, and remind them
of everything that they might be giving up.

14:09.242 --> 14:10.609
You're right.

14:10.643 --> 14:12.511
First we gotta get them
in the same room together.

14:16.215 --> 14:18.517
<i>Regina: I think that went well.</i>

14:18.551 --> 14:20.285
I swear there's somebody whining

14:20.320 --> 14:21.453
about gentrification every meeting.

14:21.487 --> 14:24.456
God forbid East Riverside has
one less check-cashing store

14:24.490 --> 14:26.191
or bail bondsman.

14:26.225 --> 14:27.192
What are you doing?

14:27.226 --> 14:29.161
Looking through the sign-in sheet.

14:29.195 --> 14:30.329
That lady came in late, right?

14:30.363 --> 14:31.596
Uh, what does it matter?

14:31.631 --> 14:34.232
Oh, here we are. "Adrianna Vasquez."

14:34.267 --> 14:35.434
Any relation?

14:38.371 --> 14:39.438
She's my mom.

14:39.472 --> 14:41.406
You're kidding me, right?

14:41.441 --> 14:43.175
Unfortunately, I'm not.

14:43.209 --> 14:44.543
(Exhales)

14:44.577 --> 14:46.345
You knew she was against the project,

14:46.379 --> 14:48.280
and you let her come to
the meeting? Are you crazy?

14:48.314 --> 14:49.514
No. I swear.

14:49.549 --> 14:50.615
That was a surprise to me too.

14:50.650 --> 14:52.184
And I will be talking to her.

14:52.218 --> 14:53.251
Yeah, well, you better.

14:53.286 --> 14:55.287
Keep it in perspective...
it was just one meeting.

14:55.321 --> 14:56.455
I don't think you get it.

14:56.489 --> 14:59.257
This kinda stuff spreads like a virus.

14:59.292 --> 15:00.492
You need to get her under control.

15:01.594 --> 15:02.561
Now.

15:08.501 --> 15:11.203
From what I've read, I
think she might be bipolar.

15:11.237 --> 15:13.438
If her mood swings come
and go that quickly,

15:13.473 --> 15:16.308
it could be borderline
personality disorder.

15:16.342 --> 15:18.143
Is there any treatment for that?

15:18.177 --> 15:21.480
Therapy, maybe medication
to control the depression.

15:21.514 --> 15:23.615
But she's going to need a psych assessment.

15:23.649 --> 15:26.184
That's the problem. I
don't think we'll be able

15:26.219 --> 15:27.519
to get her to see a psychiatrist.

15:27.553 --> 15:29.388
Hmm.

15:29.422 --> 15:31.423
Maybe she'd be more
comfortable coming here.

15:31.457 --> 15:35.193
I have a colleague who's
a clinical psychologist.

15:35.228 --> 15:37.396
I could ask him to come in
and meet with her after-hours.

15:37.430 --> 15:38.397
Really?

15:38.431 --> 15:40.365
That would be incredible.

15:40.400 --> 15:42.534
You'd have to get her here
tomorrow night around closing.

15:42.568 --> 15:44.403
You think you can talk her into that?

15:46.205 --> 15:48.173
I'll find a way.

15:58.791 --> 15:59.758
Hey.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.161
Earth to Kathryn Kennish.

16:03.195 --> 16:04.963
Oh.

16:04.997 --> 16:06.765
I'm sorry. I was on a roll.

16:06.799 --> 16:07.932
You don't have to apologize.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.834
I'm just glad you're finally writing a book

16:09.869 --> 16:11.736
that's not about me.

16:11.771 --> 16:13.204
I finished two chapters this morning.

16:13.239 --> 16:16.007
It's amazing how productive I can be

16:16.042 --> 16:20.745
when I don't have to worry about
whether John Kennish has clean underwear.

16:24.817 --> 16:27.118
(Sighs) I'm sorry.

16:27.153 --> 16:30.822
I know how confusing this whole
thing with your dad and I must be.

16:30.856 --> 16:33.992
Hey, sister, you do not have
to explain anything to me.

16:34.026 --> 16:36.127
I totally get it.

16:36.162 --> 16:37.128
Guys suck.

16:37.163 --> 16:38.897
Yep.

16:38.931 --> 16:40.198
Sometimes they do.

16:40.232 --> 16:41.833
(Clicks tongue)

16:41.867 --> 16:42.834
You know what we need?

16:42.868 --> 16:43.935
Hmm?

16:43.969 --> 16:45.203
We need a girls' night out.

16:45.237 --> 16:47.005
Tonight, what do you say?

16:47.039 --> 16:48.840
Oh, we could see if
Regina and Daphne are busy,

16:48.874 --> 16:49.974
and Renzo...

16:50.009 --> 16:51.976
I was thinking it could
just be the two of us.

16:52.011 --> 16:56.915
- You know? Old school.
- That sounds fun.

16:56.949 --> 16:58.717
Should I make an appointment at the spa?

16:58.751 --> 17:00.885
Oh, I don't wanna interrupt
your storytelling magic.

17:00.920 --> 17:02.887
