27:15.360 --> 27:16.493
Well, you two could have at least tried.

27:17.696 --> 27:20.264
Maybe we should just call it a night.

27:20.298 --> 27:21.432
I feel pretty gross.

27:21.466 --> 27:22.600
No, we can't call it a night.

27:22.634 --> 27:24.368
We're here as a family

27:24.402 --> 27:25.603
to have fun and remember

27:25.637 --> 27:27.471
how happy we are.

27:29.608 --> 27:31.575
You know what I remember about this place?

27:31.610 --> 27:33.377
Yes! Thank you. Finally.

27:33.411 --> 27:37.448
I remember bringing you and
Toby here alone most of the time,

27:37.482 --> 27:39.450
because your dad was
always out on the road.

27:39.484 --> 27:41.719
Not exactly what I was going for.

27:41.753 --> 27:44.588
Well, you know what I remember?

27:44.623 --> 27:47.691
I remember all the
passive-aggressive guilt trips I got

27:47.726 --> 27:50.361
because I was off doing my job.

27:50.395 --> 27:52.596
A job that has given
this family everything,

27:52.631 --> 27:55.466
including, I might add, your new book deal.

27:57.235 --> 27:58.302
(Exhales)

27:58.336 --> 28:00.437
Why don't you two go play in the arcade?

28:00.472 --> 28:01.605
Yeah, here's a couple of bucks.

28:01.640 --> 28:03.440
Knock yourself out.

28:10.315 --> 28:12.683
If this guy doesn't come soon, my
mom is gonna know something is up.

28:12.717 --> 28:14.518
<i>- He should be here any minute.
- (Thuds)</i>

28:14.552 --> 28:15.619
<i>Yvette: Oh, no, you don't!</i>

28:15.654 --> 28:18.522
<i>- You just back off!
- (Loud thud)</i>

28:18.556 --> 28:20.557
What's the matter?

28:20.592 --> 28:23.360
(Breathes deeply)

28:23.395 --> 28:24.428
Sharee, let's go.

28:24.462 --> 28:25.696
- Mom, wait.
- No.

28:25.730 --> 28:27.298
These people, they're trying to lock me up.

28:27.332 --> 28:28.599
It's not like that.

28:28.633 --> 28:30.301
Please, they just wanna talk.

28:30.335 --> 28:31.635
I said we are going now.

28:44.783 --> 28:46.450
Is Jorge here?

28:47.652 --> 28:49.253
Any of the other nurses?

28:49.287 --> 28:51.488
No, just us. Why?

28:53.458 --> 28:54.525
Call 9-1-1.

28:55.760 --> 28:56.660
(Gasps) Oh, my God!

28:56.695 --> 28:57.661
She stabbed you.

28:57.696 --> 28:59.229
Oh, no no.

28:59.264 --> 29:00.364
Oh, Dr. J.

29:00.398 --> 29:02.466
(Gasping breaths, groans)

29:02.500 --> 29:04.468
(Murmurs)

29:08.296 --> 29:10.130
I texted 9-1-1. They're on their way.

29:10.164 --> 29:12.065
I need your help.

29:13.078 --> 29:14.879
It's a tension pneumothorax.

29:16.181 --> 29:18.149
Pretty soon I won't be able to breathe.

29:18.183 --> 29:20.117
I don't... I don't understand.

29:20.152 --> 29:23.120
Air is getting into my chest...

29:23.155 --> 29:25.256
(Gasping breaths) ... Pressing on my lungs.

29:25.290 --> 29:27.058
What should I do?

29:27.092 --> 29:30.928
(Inhales deeply) Get my
medical kit over there.

29:40.238 --> 29:42.306
Take the needle...

29:42.340 --> 29:44.041
Open my shirt...

29:45.077 --> 29:47.278
and take the plunger out.

29:47.312 --> 29:49.113
Oh, my God.

29:49.147 --> 29:51.048
(Gulps)

29:51.083 --> 29:53.217
- Like this?
- Yeah.

29:53.251 --> 29:54.385
Now, use your fingers

29:54.419 --> 29:57.054
and find the top of my rib cage...

29:57.089 --> 29:59.924
<i>second intercostal space.</i>

30:01.293 --> 30:04.061
Second and third rib.

30:05.997 --> 30:08.032
There. Okay...

30:08.066 --> 30:09.233
Insert the needle.

30:09.267 --> 30:11.202
Wait, you want...

30:11.236 --> 30:13.170
- you want me to...
- Pop it.

30:13.205 --> 30:14.305
(Inhales sharply) Like a balloon.

30:14.339 --> 30:16.207
That can't be right.

30:16.241 --> 30:18.075
It's the only way.

30:18.110 --> 30:20.411
<i>(Gasping)</i>

30:22.981 --> 30:24.381
No no no no.

30:24.416 --> 30:26.951
I... I can't do that.

30:26.985 --> 30:29.053
The paramedics will be here any second.

30:29.087 --> 30:30.221
I... it can't wait.

30:30.255 --> 30:32.156
Can't breathe.

30:32.190 --> 30:34.992
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

30:40.465 --> 30:42.433
- (Exhales)
- (Moaning)

30:48.240 --> 30:49.406
(Exhales deeply)

30:49.441 --> 30:51.008
(Shakily) Do it.

30:53.145 --> 30:54.178
(Groans loudly)

30:54.212 --> 30:56.046
- (Inhales deeply)
- (Air hissing)

30:56.081 --> 30:58.282
(Exhales deeply)

30:58.316 --> 31:01.285
<i>(Breathes deeply)</i>

31:04.156 --> 31:05.289
Okay.

31:06.509 --> 31:08.310
Now what?

31:08.345 --> 31:11.146
We wait.

31:11.181 --> 31:13.148
<i>(Ambulance sirens wailing)</i>

31:26.062 --> 31:28.230
Did you hire me because I'm latina?

31:28.265 --> 31:30.032
What are you talking about?

31:30.066 --> 31:31.367
You know what I mean.

31:31.401 --> 31:33.369
Is that why you wanted me on the team?

31:33.403 --> 31:36.038
You been talking to your mom, haven't you?

31:36.072 --> 31:38.374
I told you. Like a virus.

31:38.408 --> 31:40.409
Just tell me the truth.

31:40.443 --> 31:43.045
You brought East Riverside to me.

31:43.079 --> 31:46.048
I brought you one building.

31:46.082 --> 31:48.284
You didn't tell me about
your plans for development

31:48.318 --> 31:51.186
until after I signed a contract
to work for you exclusively.

31:52.355 --> 31:54.089
You came to me for a loan.

31:54.124 --> 31:55.257
I wanted something in return.

31:57.093 --> 31:58.427
(Exhales) What do you want me to say?

31:58.461 --> 32:01.430
Do I think you have
talent as a designer? Yes.

32:01.464 --> 32:03.198
Does it help me that you're
from the neighborhood?

32:03.233 --> 32:04.333
Yes.

32:04.367 --> 32:07.136
I will find a way to
get you back your money.

32:07.203 --> 32:09.204
Aw, come on. You're really
gonna throw this all away?

32:09.239 --> 32:11.307
<i>This is how business works.</i>

32:11.341 --> 32:13.142
I'm using you; You're using me.

32:13.176 --> 32:16.011
The people of East Riverside...
they get the benefit.

32:16.046 --> 32:17.446
Well, that's gonna have
to happen without me.

32:17.480 --> 32:19.381
(Exhales)

32:19.416 --> 32:21.283
I guess if that's the way you feel, fine.

32:21.318 --> 32:23.218
But at least take the
night to think about it.

32:23.253 --> 32:24.286
I don't need the night.

32:24.321 --> 32:27.122
Are you sure?

32:27.157 --> 32:30.125
'Cause breach of contract
suits, they're complicated.

32:30.160 --> 32:31.427
They take a lot of
money and years in court.

32:33.330 --> 32:35.464
I mean, my lawyers, they
live for that kind of stuff.

32:37.367 --> 32:39.435
I don't think they're so fun.

32:50.280 --> 32:52.247
You did good.

33:05.475 --> 33:07.411
_

33:07.427 --> 33:09.264
Oh. I don't mind.

33:11.334 --> 33:13.302
I'm sorry about Travis.

33:13.303 --> 33:16.159
_

33:18.174 --> 33:22.077
Has he ever talked to
you about his parents?

33:22.078 --> 33:24.707
_

33:24.714 --> 33:29.051
I've tried asking him
about them a few times,

33:29.085 --> 33:31.220
and he always shuts me down.

33:32.420 --> 33:38.177
_

33:38.528 --> 33:42.213
I wonder if that's why
he blew off the interview.

33:42.214 --> 33:43.256
_

33:44.434 --> 33:48.470
I think this house is his first real home.

33:48.505 --> 33:52.408
It's like he finally found a nest

33:52.442 --> 33:55.110
just in time to get kicked out of it.

33:58.048 --> 33:59.281
I don't know. Did I sign all that right?

33:59.282 --> 34:02.450
_

34:02.452 --> 34:04.153
Okay.

34:08.058 --> 34:09.257
We should have known this
was gonna be a bad plan.

34:09.292 --> 34:10.391
At least we got 'em talking.

34:10.427 --> 34:11.460
Yay us.

34:11.494 --> 34:13.429
Check it out. Is that an iPod?

34:13.463 --> 34:14.996
Where?

34:15.031 --> 34:16.331
Behind the cheetah turtle.

34:16.366 --> 34:18.000
Oh, it is so my turn.

34:19.369 --> 34:22.404
I am not gonna apologize
for wanting to have a career.

34:22.438 --> 34:25.107
When we first got married,
that was the plan, remember?

34:25.141 --> 34:27.042
And then Toby came along,

34:27.077 --> 34:29.043
and six months turned into a year.

34:29.079 --> 34:30.279
And then I got pregnant again.

34:30.313 --> 34:32.313
We never stopped to ask ourselves:

34:32.348 --> 34:34.083
Is this what we really want?

34:34.117 --> 34:36.185
I never said you had to
stay home with the kids.

34:36.219 --> 34:38.087
No, you never actually said it.

34:38.121 --> 34:40.089
Come on, John.

34:40.123 --> 34:42.424
You can't even handle me
going out of town for two days

34:42.458 --> 34:44.092
without going off the rails.

34:44.127 --> 34:45.427
You know, I'm not gonna explain that again.

34:45.462 --> 34:47.396
I've apologized like a thousand times.

34:47.429 --> 34:49.063
So why don't you just tell me

34:49.099 --> 34:51.433
what the hell it is that you want?

34:51.467 --> 34:54.168
I want you to hear me.

34:54.204 --> 34:56.338
I'm not happy.

34:56.371 --> 34:58.073
And I don't think you are either.

34:58.108 --> 34:59.975
What do you want me to say?

35:00.009 --> 35:01.343
I'm not happy? Okay. I'm not happy.

35:01.377 --> 35:03.078
Thank you.

35:03.113 --> 35:04.246
Do you know why I'm not happy?

35:04.280 --> 35:07.049
I'm not happy, because you keep telling me

35:07.083 --> 35:08.217
how unhappy you are.

35:11.321 --> 35:12.287
<i>Toby: You're almost there.</i>

35:12.322 --> 35:13.455
Now just drop the claw.

35:18.228 --> 35:19.361
<i>John: Let's look at the scoreboard.</i>

35:19.395 --> 35:22.097
I've made one mistake in 20 years.

35:22.132 --> 35:24.366
Other than that, I've been
a pretty damn good husband.

35:24.400 --> 35:27.102
And I have given you a great life.

35:27.137 --> 35:28.470
You're a great provider.

35:28.505 --> 35:30.072
You are.

35:30.106 --> 35:32.074
But let's just be honest.

35:32.108 --> 35:34.243
We don't have very much in common anymore.

35:34.277 --> 35:35.310
Except for the kids.

35:35.345 --> 35:37.479
You're being ridiculous!
We have tons in common.

35:37.514 --> 35:39.348
Like what exactly?

35:39.382 --> 35:42.017
I don't know. Like our
friends, like the club.

35:42.051 --> 35:43.452
Do you know how sad that sounds?

35:43.486 --> 35:45.454
Is that what we're gonna
do for the next 30 years?

35:45.488 --> 35:48.023
Sit around the country club till we die?

35:48.057 --> 35:50.125
And what would be so bad about that?

35:50.160 --> 35:51.293
Last chance.

35:51.327 --> 35:53.228
Okay.

35:53.263 --> 35:55.330
I think I'm getting the hang of it.

36:01.137 --> 36:02.337
- You got it! Sweet!
- Aah!

36:02.372 --> 36:04.106
Now just get it to the drop zone.

36:04.140 --> 36:06.208
Aah.

36:06.242 --> 36:08.043
Dude, you totally had it.

36:10.146 --> 36:11.346
<i>Hey.</i>

36:11.381 --> 36:14.082
- What's wrong?
- (Exhales)

36:14.117 --> 36:15.350
We're going in different directions.

36:15.385 --> 36:18.353
No. You are going in a different direction.

36:18.388 --> 36:20.289
I am where I have always been.

36:20.323 --> 36:22.424
And if all of a sudden, that
is not good enough for you,

36:22.458 --> 36:24.193
then that is your problem.

36:24.227 --> 36:25.394
Guys.

36:25.428 --> 36:27.129
There's something wrong with Bay.

36:30.099 --> 36:31.466
<i>- Honey, what is it?
- I... I don't know.</i>

36:31.501 --> 36:33.168
But I can't move my fingers.

36:52.398 --> 36:55.166
I swear I didn't know.

36:55.201 --> 36:58.336
She was talking crazy the
whole way home from the clinic.

36:58.370 --> 37:00.338
I didn't know anything until
the cops came to arrest her.

37:02.308 --> 37:04.209
That poor doctor.

37:04.243 --> 37:06.010
He was just trying to help us.

37:06.045 --> 37:08.179
He's gonna be okay.

37:10.983 --> 37:12.951
I feel so bad.

37:15.154 --> 37:16.354
I should have known better.

37:16.388 --> 37:20.091
I should have gotten
her help a long time ago.

37:24.163 --> 37:26.030
My mom stabbed someone.

37:26.065 --> 37:28.299
Sharee, it's not your fault.

37:28.334 --> 37:30.401
What if she goes to jail?

37:30.436 --> 37:32.403
I mean...

37:34.139 --> 37:35.306
What's gonna happen to me?

37:44.183 --> 37:46.985
She has two lacerated tendons.
Middle and index fingers.

37:47.019 --> 37:49.320
It's likely that they were partially
severed from the original injury.

37:49.355 --> 37:51.155
How come we didn't know about that?

37:51.190 --> 37:54.392
The E.R. made the best guess they
could before they sewed her up.

37:54.426 --> 37:56.961
But there's really no way
for us to tell for sure

37:56.996 --> 37:58.296
until something like this happens.

37:58.330 --> 38:00.865
So...

38:00.870 --> 38:02.871
- What do we do?
- We'll get in there

38:02.905 --> 38:04.839
and we'll surgically repair the tendons.

38:04.874 --> 38:06.241
And what's the recovery time?

38:06.275 --> 38:08.943
We can usually expect movement
within a couple months.

38:10.012 --> 38:11.212
Bay's an artist.

38:11.247 --> 38:13.248
She uses her right hand for everything.

38:15.184 --> 38:17.152
Will she still be able to paint and draw?

38:20.122 --> 38:21.189
We'll do our best.

38:32.867 --> 38:34.924
_

38:37.340 --> 38:40.356
_

38:41.661 --> 38:44.969
_

38:44.970 --> 38:47.999
_

38:48.000 --> 38:51.532
_

38:51.533 --> 38:55.161
_

38:55.162 --> 38:59.131
_

39:00.214 --> 39:02.841
_

39:02.842 --> 39:06.113
_

39:08.005 --> 39:09.326
_

39:10.905 --> 39:14.536
_

39:14.537 --> 39:16.092
_

39:17.340 --> 39:19.313
_

39:22.318 --> 39:23.918
Oh.

39:23.919 --> 39:25.050
_

39:26.021 --> 39:26.988
Hey.

39:31.945 --> 39:35.262
_

39:35.263 --> 39:38.608
_

39:38.610 --> 39:40.835
Aw, darn.

39:40.869 --> 39:43.037
I already asked out the
cute history teacher.

39:46.275 --> 39:47.909
I'm... I'm kidding.

39:49.078 --> 39:50.011
(Laughs)

39:52.220 --> 39:53.539
_

39:53.540 --> 39:55.730
_

39:55.884 --> 39:56.851
Okay.

39:58.921 --> 40:00.054
See you later.

40:07.062 --> 40:08.029
I'll see you at the house.

40:08.063 --> 40:10.999
What? Why?

40:11.033 --> 40:13.134
Kathryn, I'm coming home.

40:13.168 --> 40:16.170
Bay needs us right now. Both of us.

40:16.205 --> 40:17.338
I agree.

40:17.373 --> 40:21.009
But it doesn't mean that
we have to live together.

40:21.043 --> 40:23.144
Okay, this is ridiculous. All right?

40:23.178 --> 40:25.146
- Stop playing games.
- I'm not playing games.

40:25.180 --> 40:27.081
I've been thinking about
what you said last night.

40:27.116 --> 40:29.083
And...

40:29.118 --> 40:30.151
Maybe you're right.

40:30.185 --> 40:33.288
- Okay, look...
- Maybe it is my problem.

40:33.322 --> 40:36.190
I'm the one who's changed.

40:36.225 --> 40:39.193
And this life that we've created...

40:41.930 --> 40:44.032
it's not the life I want anymore.

40:52.041 --> 40:54.275
Even if we had the room,

40:54.310 --> 40:57.045
Sharee has to go to an actual foster home.

40:58.881 --> 41:01.916
She has this great aunt
that she's never met

41:01.950 --> 41:04.052
coming in from Miami to live with her.

41:04.086 --> 41:05.119
Well, she'll be with relatives.

41:05.154 --> 41:06.120
That'll be good for her.

41:06.155 --> 41:08.056
(Sighs)

41:08.090 --> 41:09.223
I guess.

41:09.258 --> 41:12.293
I just wanted her to see what it was like

41:12.328 --> 41:14.295
to be a part of a real family.

41:14.330 --> 41:16.197
And not just us.

41:16.231 --> 41:19.334
Everyone deserves the
royal Kennish treatment

41:19.368 --> 41:22.103
at least once.

41:23.272 --> 41:24.272
Ahem.

41:24.306 --> 41:27.075
There's something I have to tell you.

41:27.109 --> 41:30.044
I was sort of hoping that
it would work itself out,

41:30.079 --> 41:31.979
but now I'm not so sure.

41:32.014 --> 41:34.282
What's going on?

41:36.018 --> 41:37.251
It's about John and Kathryn.

41:40.055 --> 41:42.023
When we came home from
Sharee's the other night...

41:42.057 --> 41:43.191
<i>(Piano music playing)</i>

41:43.225 --> 41:44.359
<i>♪ How did this happen again? ♪</i>

41:44.393 --> 41:46.027
<i>(TV announcer speaking indistinctly)</i>

41:46.061 --> 41:48.363
<i>♪ When did the room start to spin? ♪</i>

41:48.397 --> 41:50.198
<i>♪ Out of focus ♪</i>

41:50.232 --> 41:53.901
<i>♪ and crashing the breezes ♪</i>

41:53.936 --> 41:56.003
<i>♪ I thought we'd figured it out ♪</i>

41:56.038 --> 41:58.906
<i>♪ thought our hearts finally found ♪</i>

41:58.941 --> 42:03.845
<i>♪ one love that trumped every reason ♪</i>

42:09.184 --> 42:14.188
<i>♪ one love that trumped every reason ♪</i>

42:14.223 --> 42:18.993
<i>- ♪ one love that trumped every reason to go ♪
- (Grunting)</i>

42:19.027 --> 42:25.333
<i>♪ One love that trumped
every reason to go ♪</i>

